snippet: The body of a teenager tested positive for the virus, ending Liberia’s Ebola-free status, said the deputy minister for health, and raising fresh concerns.
abstract: Two new Ebola cases are discovered in Libera less than two months after World Health Organization declared country to be free of virus.
lead_paragraph: The body of a teenager tested positive for the virus, ending Liberia’s Ebola-free status, said the deputy minister for health, and raising fresh concerns.

headline.main: New Cases of Ebola Put an End to Liberia’s Status as Virus-Free
